Third-party attributions
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project's soft-DTW implementation is an independent re-implementation
informed by the following works. NONE of the third-party code below is vendored,
copied, or redistributed in this repository. They are cited for attribution and
algorithmic provenance only.

1. soft-DTW (forward recursion and the Cuturi-Blondel gradient algorithm)
   Mathieu Blondel, "soft-dtw"  --  https://github.com/mblondel/soft-dtw
   License: BSD-2-Clause (verified against the upstream LICENSE, 2026-05-29).
   Reference: M. Cuturi, M. Blondel. "Soft-DTW: a Differentiable Loss Function
   for Time-Series." ICML 2017. arXiv:1703.01541
   Divergence form: M. Blondel, A. Mensch, J.-P. Vert. "Differentiable Divergences
   Between Time Series." AISTATS 2021. arXiv:2010.08354

2. CUDA fast-path (OPTIONAL, lazy-imported only when `pytorch_softdtw_cuda` is importable
   AND a CUDA device is present; not on PyPI, so the user installs it themselves; never
   vendored, never a hard dependency)
   Mehran Maghoumi, "pytorch-softdtw-cuda"
   https://github.com/Maghoumi/pytorch-softdtw-cuda
   License: MIT (verified against the upstream LICENSE, 2026-05-29).

dtwarp's default CPU path uses its own pure-PyTorch implementation and does not
require either project to be installed.
